definition.value: A member of the class of isoquinolines carrying two methoxy substituents at positions 6 and 7.

A monocarboxylic acid that is butanoic acid substituted by an amino group at position 4 and a 4-chlorophenyl group at position 3. It acts as a central nervous system depressant, GABA agonist and muscle relaxant.
A dTDP-sugar having 6-deoxy-alpha-D-allose as the sugar portion.
A dTDP-sugar having 3,6-dideoxy-3-dimethylamino-alpha-D-glucose (alpha-D-mycaminose) as the sugar component.
A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of lithocholic acid.
A cholanic acid conjugate anion that is the conjugate base of glycocholic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of cholic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of ferulic acid.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is pyruvic acid substituted by a 1H-indol-3-yl group at position 3. It has been found in Lycopersicon esculentum
A quinate that is the conjugate base of (-)-quinic acid.
The parent compound of the aminoxyl group of radicals.
An inorganic anion that is the conjugate base of hydroxylamine, arising from deprotonation of the amino function.
